# Prism event listener — copy to event-listener.properties to enable.
#
# This registers the `prism-events` EventListenerFactory provided by the
# Prism plugin. Once enabled, Trino emits a structured JSON line per query
# on the SLF4J logger `io.prism.events` (log level INFO). Operators can
# route that logger to any existing sink (file, Fluent Bit, Vector, Kafka)
# via their Log4j2/Logback config — no Prism-specific audit pipe required.
#
# Prism fields emitted (as JSON keys on the log line):
#   prism.acceleration_used       — did the query hit a Rust worker (bool)
#   prism.bytes_scanned           — bytes read from object store
#   prism.rows_produced           — rows returned by workers
#   prism.worker_ids              — comma-separated worker ids
#   prism.rust_runtime_ms         — ms spent in Rust execution
#   prism.substrait_plan_bytes    — size of shipped Substrait plan
#   prism.connector_fallback_reason — set when pushdown was rejected
#
# Multiple event listeners can coexist: this one does not replace your
# cluster's existing Kafka/audit EventListener, it runs alongside it.

event-listener.name=prism-events
